ladybird9 — the Ladybird browser on 9front

v0.2.0
  Interactive browser chrome — a tab strip, address bar, and back/forward/
  reload/stop, drawn presenter-side in gl9win2 (`ladybird` with no URL opens a
  usable window). Bundled DejaVu fonts (no more hand-drawn fallback; broad
  Unicode). Persistent-profile groundwork (SQLite unix-none VFS). The four
  deferred engine features now enabled: WebGL (gl9/Mesa softpipe, surfaceless
  FBO + readback — no GPU), JPEG-XL + AVIF decode (libjxl/highway, libavif/
  dav1d), and <video>/<audio> decode (ffmpeg 7.1.1, C-only). HTTPS works out of
  the box now — the Mozilla CA roots are bundled (share/ca.pem) and passed via
  --certificate, so no hand-fetching a bundle into /sys/lib/tls (issue #23).
  Built against the audited cc9 runtime (memory-safety / data-loss / security /
  correctness fixes). Still 1:1 with upstream — additive PLAN9 arms + new
  platform files only.

  Stability + correctness pass (cc9 runtime + port):
  - Images render. Skia's skcms_Parse overflowed a stack buffer under cc9 on
    every ICC-profiled image, killing the ImageDecoder; ICC parsing now falls
    back to sRGB on Plan 9. (Verified: local + remote PNG/JPEG render.)
  - HTTPS fixed end to end. A struct-tm ABI regression made OpenSSL read valid
    certs as expired; reverted, with SDL3 taking its own tm_gmtoff-free path.
    Works with no --certificate flag (curl's built-in /sys/lib/tls/ca.pem).
  - IPC shm hardening: adopt an already-attached #g pool instead of failing
    "segments overlap"; never detach a pool a sibling thread is still reading
    (use-after-detach crash); LRU-bound idle pools. These killed a family of
    mid-navigation crashes (the "terminal text over the browser" overlay was a
    helper suicide note drawn on the page — also fixed by keeping helper stderr
    off the window).
  - "write on closed pipe" is now SIGPIPE (EPIPE), not a fatal fault.
  - Networking: RFC 6761 .localhost resolution; getsockname() reports the real
    port after an ephemeral bind (Python test servers work). Concurrent curl
    connections are capped so a heavy page can't exhaust the process table.
  - UI: macOS-style Super chords (Super-L focus+select-all, Super-T/W/R);
    Plan 9 line editing (Ctrl-A/E/U) in the address bar; address-bar descenders
    no longer clipped.
  - Real SDL3 3.2.24 (was a stub): all 9 GamepadAPI tests pass, matching macOS.

  Known limitations: heavy client-rendered SPAs (e.g. youtube.com) do not
  settle and can drive a small box out of memory; static and moderate sites
  (Wikipedia, news, forums) render fully with images.

v0.1.0
  First release. A real multi-process Ladybird (LadybirdBrowser/ladybird,
  pinned master 8cc5d7a5ff) cross-compiled to native Plan 9 amd64 a.out via
  the cc9 toolchain — the full engine: LibWeb, LibJS (AsmInt), Skia CPU raster,
  ICU, curl+OpenSSL, the 10 Rust crates. Runs as UI + WebContent + Compositor +
  RequestServer + ImageDecoder over TransportPlan9 IPC (shm via #g named
  segments, fd-passing via /srv).

  - Headless: `ladybird --headless --screenshot-path shot.png <url>` renders a
    live page to a PNG (run the binary at /usr/glenda/ladybird9/bin/ladybird).
  - Interactive: `ladybird <url>` opens a libdraw window via the gl9win2
    presenter (Skia BGRA frames streamed as GL9B; mouse/keyboard/scroll flow
    back).

  Known limitations (see ladybird9/parity/deferrals.md): no <video>/<audio>
  (ffmpeg not built), no WebGL (no GPU), no JPEG-XL/AVIF; SQL database disabled
  (Plan 9 SQLite locking) and the profile is temporary — the launcher passes
  --disable-sql-database --temporary-profile, so history/cookies do not persist
  yet (a persistent profile wedges on the Plan 9 exclusive profile lock after a
  crash). gl9win2 ships package-private at /usr/glenda/ladybird9/bin/gl9win2.
